        "subject": "LU-13643 ldlm: implement special aging for ACTIVE_WRITER locks",
        "message": "LU-13643 ldlm: implement special aging for ACTIVE_WRITER locks\n\nActive writer locks should not be cancelled immediately, so\nclients can reuse them, but they should be cancelled very\nquickly because their presence prevents immediate mirror\nfiles from becoming fully redundant.\n\nTrack them specially and run LRU pruning aggressively when\nthey're present, so we can respect short age limits.\n\nDefault of 1 second.\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Id1e4a9ad1c53ae8d928c5570396ee512199ee79e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master",
      "description": "Rebase"
    }
